<p><ent>Wrath</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Wrath
<hw>Wrath</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To anger; to enrage; -- also used
impersonally.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧I will not
<xex>wrathen</xex> him.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If him <qex>wratheth</qex>, be ywar and his way shun.</q>
<rj><qau>Piers Plowman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wrathful</ent>⟦br⟧
